The CI errors are coming from **two separate issues**.

## 1. Root-relative asset paths

Your pages use paths like:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/qeepp.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/qeepp-charts.css" />
<link rel="icon" href="/assets/icons/qeepp-fav.ico" />
```

Lychee is checking local files, not a live web server, so `/assets/...` cannot be resolved in that context.

### Fix

For local HTML files in your repo, change those to **relative paths**:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/qeepp.css" />
<link rel="stylesheet" href="assets/css/qeepp-charts.css" />
<link rel="icon" href="assets/icons/qeepp-fav.ico" />
```

Use `../assets/...` only inside partials or nested folders if needed.
For top-level pages like `starfish-diagram.html`, `radar-chart.html`, `trends-chart.html`, `resources.html`, etc., use:

```html
assets/css/qeepp.css
assets/css/qeepp-charts.css
assets/icons/qeepp-fav.ico
```

---

## 2. Extensionless internal links in raw HTML

You now link like this:

```html
<a href="assessment-methodology">...</a>
<a href="starfish-diagram">...</a>
<a href="radar-chart">...</a>
```

These work on the live site because your hosting rewrites them, but Lychee is opening local files from disk, so it expects actual file names.

### Fix

Inside local HTML source, use the real file names:

```html
<a href="assessment-methodology.html">...</a>
<a href="starfish-diagram.html">...</a>
<a href="radar-chart.html">...</a>
<a href="trends-chart.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-assessment.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-diagnostic-interview.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-practical-assessment-framework.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-assessment-checklist.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-maturity-model.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-transformation-playbook.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-case-azure-modernization.html">...</a>
<a href="qeepp-about.html">...</a>
<a href="faq.html">...</a>
```

This is the main reason for all these errors:

* `Cannot find file: .../assessment-methodology`
* `Cannot find file: .../starfish-diagram`
* `Cannot find file: .../trends-chart`

---

## Why this happens

Your hosting supports pretty URLs, but the CI checker is validating the **repository files directly**. So:

* live site prefers `/faq`
* repo checker needs `faq.html`

That is normal.

---

## Best practical rule

Use this in the HTML source:

* **assets:** relative paths like `assets/css/...`
* **internal page links:** actual filenames like `radar-chart.html`

Use canonical tags and sitemap for the clean public URLs.

So this is fine:

```html
<link rel="canonical" href="https://qeepp.com/radar-chart" />
<a href="radar-chart.html">QEEPP Radar</a>
```

That is usually the best static-site compromise.

